02:38.810 --> 02:40.856
-KMF 295 REQUESTING
IMMEDIATE BACKUP.

02:40.986 --> 02:42.249
-WHAT'S YOUR 20, MITCH?

02:42.379 --> 02:44.338
-ON TOWER 18,
ALL AVAILABLE UNITS.

02:45.817 --> 02:47.645
-RESCUE ONE,
REQUESTING BACKUP.

02:56.176 --> 02:59.179
-[SIREN WAILING]

03:11.278 --> 03:12.757
-RESCUE TWO, EN ROUTE.

03:44.528 --> 03:46.356
-WOMAN:
NICE SAVE, MITCH!

03:46.487 --> 03:48.358
-A BAG, OKAY.
IT'S A BAG.

03:48.489 --> 03:51.840
VERY FUNNY.
HA HA HA.

04:03.939 --> 04:07.464
-[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

04:10.293 --> 04:11.294
-HEY, DAD.

04:11.860 --> 04:12.817
WHAT ARE YOU WRITING?

04:14.819 --> 04:16.430
DAD, WHY DON'T YOU
COME OUT OF THE STONE AGE

04:16.560 --> 04:18.475
AND GET A COMPUTER
LIKE ALL THE OTHER WRITERS?

04:18.606 --> 04:21.522
-I'VE WRITTEN 10 NOVELS
AND 18 MOVIES ON THIS MACHINE,
MATT.

04:22.087 --> 04:23.741
NOT ABOUT TO ABANDON IT NOW.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.706
-WELL, MAYBE I SHOULD HAVE
BEEN BORN A MACHINE.

04:31.836 --> 04:36.058
-[ENGINE REVVING]

04:43.500 --> 04:44.588
-MATTHEW!

04:44.719 --> 04:47.809
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

04:48.331 --> 04:52.117
-[RESPONDING IN FRENCH]

04:55.904 --> 04:58.123
-PLEASE, MATTHEW,
BE CAREFUL!

05:04.129 --> 05:06.001
-DON'T SAY A WORD.

05:09.134 --> 05:11.485
-HEY, ANY OF US
WOULD HAVE DONE
THE SAME THING, MITCH.

05:11.615 --> 05:12.877
-YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT.

05:13.008 --> 05:14.314
HEY, BETTER TO BE SAFE
THAN SORRY.

05:28.066 --> 05:32.593
-[ALL LAUGHING]

05:32.723 --> 05:34.290
-VERY FUNNY.

05:38.381 --> 05:41.776
-YEP, IT'S IN
A GREAT LOCATION,
JUST ACROSS FROM THE BEACH.

05:41.906 --> 05:44.561
IT'S SPACIOUS,
AND THE BEST PART IS,

05:44.692 --> 05:46.476
I CAN AFFORD IT.
[LAUGHS]

05:46.607 --> 05:48.217
I DON'T NEED
TO GET A ROOMMATE.

05:48.348 --> 05:50.524
-THAT'S GREAT!
I JUST GOT A PLACE TOO.

05:50.654 --> 05:53.527
AND HERE IS TO LIVING ALONE.

05:53.657 --> 05:56.704
NO ONE TO CRITICIZE YOU,
ANTAGONIZE YOU.

05:56.834 --> 05:59.054
-BORROW YOUR CLOTHES,
EAT YOUR FOOD.

05:59.184 --> 06:00.577
I'LL TOAST TO THAT.

06:00.708 --> 06:02.405
HERE'S TO LIVING ALONE!
-TO LIVING ALONE! WHOO!

06:05.190 --> 06:06.627
OH MY GOD.

06:07.149 --> 06:09.369
THEY'RE NEVER
GOING TO LET MITCH
LIVE THIS ONE DOWN.

06:09.499 --> 06:12.154
-I MEAN, THEY COULD
AT LEAST CLEAN UP
AFTER THEMSELVES.

06:12.284 --> 06:14.286
I MEAN, WE DON'T HAVE
A MAID AROUND HERE.

06:14.896 --> 06:15.940
-COULD HAVE FOOLED ME.

06:17.986 --> 06:20.249
[GIGGLES]

06:30.781 --> 06:31.869
-HEY, SUMMER.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.393
HEY, LOOSEN UP
WITH THAT THING.

06:33.523 --> 06:34.872
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO DROWN IN THE SAND.

06:35.525 --> 06:37.788
-I'M JUST SO NERVOUS.
I'VE BEEN LOOKING EVERYWHERE
FOR YOU.

06:37.919 --> 06:40.138
-YEAH, MY FATHER'S
ON MY CASE AGAIN.

06:40.269 --> 06:42.489
HE SAYS I NEVER FINISH
ANYTHING I START.

06:43.490 --> 06:45.492
I SWEAR THE DAY
I GRADUATE ROOKIE SCHOOL,

06:45.622 --> 06:48.320
I'M GONNA TAKE
THIS RESCUE CAN AND SHOVE IT
RIGHT UP HIS TYPEWRITER.

06:48.973 --> 06:50.410
-LOOKS LIKE YOU LUCKED OUT

06:50.540 --> 06:51.976
TO BEAT ME IN
THE QUALIFYING SWIM, BRODY.

06:52.107 --> 06:53.543
CONGRATULATIONS.

06:54.109 --> 06:55.502
I GOTTA TELL YOU,
I DON'T THINK LUCK

06:55.632 --> 06:56.938
IS GONNA KEEP YOU THROUGH
THIS TIME, PAL.

06:57.068 --> 06:58.461
IF YOU'RE GONNA BE
ROOKIE OF THE YEAR,

06:58.592 --> 06:59.593
YOU'RE JUST GONNA
HAVE TO GO THROUGH ME.

07:00.463 --> 07:02.465
-YOU'RE SUCH A TORTOISE
IN THE WATER, CLINT.

07:03.423 --> 07:04.989
I'LL SWIM RIGHT AROUND YOU.

07:12.083 --> 07:13.607
-HEY, MITCH! MITCH!
-MORNING.

07:13.737 --> 07:15.913
-GUIDO, HOW ARE YOU?
-I'M A'GONNA SWIM FOR YOU.

07:16.044 --> 07:18.220
I'VE BEEN DAY AND NIGHT
PRACTICING IN THE WATER.

07:18.350 --> 07:19.482
JUST LOOK
AT THIS BODY, HUH?

07:19.613 --> 07:20.875
AND LOOK AT THESE MUSCLES,
HUH?

07:21.005 --> 07:22.224
SO MANY OF THEM,
ALL IN ONE PLACE, HUH?

07:22.354 --> 07:23.660
-GUIDO, I APPRECIATE
YOUR ENTHUSIASM.

07:23.791 --> 07:25.314
BUT I GOT A LOT OF GUYS--
-BAH, BAH, BAH!

07:25.445 --> 07:27.098
I HAVE WHAT IT IS
YOU NEED, MITCH.

07:27.229 --> 07:29.884
SO USE ME.
USE ME TILL I AM
ALL OF ME USED UP.

07:30.014 --> 07:32.669
-I MIGHT BE ABLE TO USE YOU
IN SOME OTHER CAPACITY,

07:32.800 --> 07:33.757
IF YOU'RE INTERESTED.

07:33.888 --> 07:35.455
-AM I INTERESTED?

07:36.325 --> 07:38.327
DOES A LIFEGUARD
WEAR HIS RED SHORTS?

07:39.415 --> 07:41.635
-THANKS. MORNING!
-ALL: GOOD MORNING!

07:41.765 --> 07:43.071
-WELCOME TO ROOKIE SCHOOL.

07:44.028 --> 07:47.336
LAST YEAR, 16,934 PEOPLE

07:47.467 --> 07:48.990
WERE ABLE TO GO HOME
FROM THE BEACH

07:49.120 --> 07:51.558
BECAUSE L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARDS
SAVED THEIR LIVES.

07:51.688 --> 07:53.951
THE RECORD FOR RESCUES
IN ONE DAY

07:54.082 --> 07:57.172
BY ONE LIFEGUARD
IS 78.

07:57.868 --> 07:59.914
SOMEONE'S LIFE
MAY DEPEND

08:00.044 --> 08:01.219
ON WHAT YOU LEARN HERE.

08:01.350 --> 08:03.047
SO PAY ATTENTION.

08:04.309 --> 08:05.920
-EVERYTHING YOU DO
FROM THIS MOMENT FORWARD

08:06.050 --> 08:08.139
WILL BE OBSERVED
AND EVALUATED.

08:08.662 --> 08:11.099
IF YOU FAIL
A WRITTEN EXAMINATION
OR A PHYSICAL DRILL,

08:11.229 --> 08:12.143
YOU WILL BE DISMISSED.

08:13.144 --> 08:14.929
THOSE OF YOU
WHO ARE NOT DISMISSED

08:15.451 --> 08:18.149
OR WHO DON'T QUIT
DURING THE NEXT TWO WEEKS
OF INTENSE TRAINING

08:18.280 --> 08:20.151
WILL BE DRAFTED TO WORK
ON VARIOUS BEACHES.

08:20.804 --> 08:22.676
THE ONE WHO IS VOTED
ROOKIE OF THE YEAR

08:22.806 --> 08:25.330
WILL BE ABLE TO SELECT
HIS OR HER OWN BEACH.

08:25.853 --> 08:28.029
-MITCH:
YOU'LL BE LEARNING ABOUT
LIFE-SAVING TECHNIQUES,

08:28.159 --> 08:31.772
LIFE-SAVING EQUIPMENT,
C.P.R.,

08:31.902 --> 08:35.123
MOUTH-TO-MOUTH RESUSCITATION,
FIRST AID.

08:35.775 --> 08:40.736
BUT WHAT WE CAN'T TEACH YOU
IS RESPONSIBILITY.
-[BOTH LAUGH]

08:42.347 --> 08:44.959
-HELLO.
DID I SAY SOMETHING FUNNY?

08:45.089 --> 08:46.569
-UH, NO, SIR.

08:47.178 --> 08:48.876
-UM, SORRY,
IT WAS MY FAULT.

08:49.006 --> 08:50.268
I SAID SOMETHING TO HER.

08:51.792 --> 08:53.707
-WHY DON'T YOU SHARE IT
WITH THE REST OF US?

08:55.578 --> 08:57.145
-I WAS JUST WONDERING
WHICH OF YOU

08:57.275 --> 08:59.843
WOULD BE MY PARTNER
TO LEARN MOUTH-TO-MOUTH.

09:05.936 --> 09:06.850
-MISTER?

09:08.156 --> 09:09.940
-UH, BRODY.
MATT BRODY.

09:10.941 --> 09:12.029
-MR. BRODY,

09:12.813 --> 09:15.380
MOUTH-TO-MOUTH RESUSCITATION
IS NOT KISSING.

09:16.077 --> 09:18.340
A LIFEGUARD MAY HAVE TO GIVE
MOUTH-TO-MOUTH RESUSCITATION

09:18.470 --> 09:20.908
TO A 250 POUND TRUCK DRIVER

09:21.038 --> 09:22.866
OR A TWO-YEAR-OLD CHILD.

09:22.997 --> 09:25.695
IT IS NOT A SITUATION
WHERE ONE CHOOSES A PARTNER.

09:26.348 --> 09:29.046
THIS IS NOT "THE DATING GAME."
IS THAT CLEAR?

09:31.875 --> 09:34.617
-THE GAUNTLET IS
A LIFEGUARD OBSTACLE COURSE.

09:35.139 --> 09:36.750
YOU'LL RUN IT TWICE--

09:36.880 --> 09:39.535
FIRST TIME FOR FUN
AND JUST TO GET
THE FEEL OF IT.

09:39.666 --> 09:42.712
SECOND TIME WILL BE
AT THE COMPLETION
OF ROOKIE SCHOOL.

09:43.321 --> 09:45.541
IT WILL BE THE ULTIMATE
PASS-FAIL TEST.

