12:32.882 --> 12:33.970
-SUMMER!

12:34.971 --> 12:36.886
SUMMER, HI.

12:37.495 --> 12:38.540
I'M C.J.

12:39.106 --> 12:41.325
-YEAH, I GUESS EVERYBODY KNOWS
WHO I AM NOW--

12:41.456 --> 12:43.458
THE ONLY ONE WHO
DIDN'T MAKE THE PIER JUMP.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.634
-YOU'RE NOT THE FIRST ROOKIE
TO BE TERRIFIED UP THERE

12:45.765 --> 12:47.157
AND YOU DEFINITELY
WON'T BE THE LAST.

12:47.288 --> 12:49.116
-YEAH, WELL, WHAT
DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

12:49.246 --> 12:51.335
IF I DON'T MAKE THE JUMP,
I DON'T GRADUATE
ROOKIE SCHOOL.

12:51.858 --> 12:53.033
-YOU'LL MAKE THE JUMP.

12:53.163 --> 12:55.209
-YEAH, THAT'S EASY
FOR YOU TO SAY.

12:55.339 --> 12:57.864
YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE TO LOOK
DOWN AT THE WATER AND--

12:57.994 --> 12:59.648
-FEEL LIKE
IT'S 100 MILES AWAY?

12:59.779 --> 13:01.302
YOUR HEART'S BEATING SO LOUD

13:01.432 --> 13:02.956
THAT YOU CAN'T HEAR
THE WAVES CRASHING BELOW?

13:03.086 --> 13:05.175
SUMMER, I WAS THE ONLY ONE
IN MY ROOKIE CLASS

13:05.306 --> 13:06.960
WHO COULDN'T
MAKE THE PIER JUMP
THE FIRST TIME OUT.

13:07.090 --> 13:09.092
-YEAH, WELL, SO HOW'D
YOU FINALLY DO IT?

13:09.701 --> 13:12.313
-I DECIDED THAT I WANTED IT
MORE THAN I WAS AFRAID OF IT.

13:13.227 --> 13:14.881
AND WHEN
THAT FINAL JUMP CAME,

13:15.011 --> 13:16.839
I JUST IMAGINED
THAT THERE WAS SOMEONE
DOWN THERE

13:16.970 --> 13:19.581
WHO WOULD DROWN IF I DIDN'T.
SO I DID.

13:28.851 --> 13:31.027
-[HUMMING]

13:31.549 --> 13:32.507
-[RUSTLING AT DOOR]

13:32.637 --> 13:34.465
-HEY, HEY!
HEY, HEY!

13:35.902 --> 13:36.903
C.J.!

13:39.035 --> 13:40.863
HOW'D YOU GET THE KEY
TO MY APARTMENT?

13:42.430 --> 13:43.866
-YOUR APARTMENT?

13:44.954 --> 13:46.347
-YEAH.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.566
-I RENTED THIS PLACE
FROM AN OLD BOYFRIEND
OF MINE,

13:48.697 --> 13:50.046
MARK--
-HARRIS?

13:50.177 --> 13:51.352
-YOU KNOW HIM?

13:51.482 --> 13:53.006
-KNOW HIM?
I DATED HIM.

13:55.138 --> 13:56.748
HE RENTED THIS APARTMENT
TO ME LAST WEEK.

13:57.401 --> 13:59.751
-I GAVE HIM FIRST AND LAST
TWO WEEKS AGO.

14:00.448 --> 14:01.405
-SO?

14:02.058 --> 14:04.321
-SO I LEASED THIS APARTMENT
BEFORE YOU DID.

14:06.193 --> 14:07.020
-WELL...

14:09.326 --> 14:10.850
I HAVE TAKEN POSSESSION.

14:12.373 --> 14:14.679
AND POSSESSION
IS NINE TENTHS OF THE LAW.

14:15.724 --> 14:17.204
-OKAY, IF YOU WANT
TO GET TECHNICAL...

14:20.860 --> 14:22.470
CONSIDER THIS POSSESSION.

14:23.210 --> 14:24.472
-OH MY...

14:28.519 --> 14:29.825
-[C.J. CHANTING]

14:49.714 --> 14:50.846
-LOOK WHAT YOU MADE ME DO.

14:52.021 --> 14:53.544
-OH, YOU SHOULDN'T
BE USING SALT.

14:53.675 --> 14:54.676
-I LIKE SALT.

14:54.806 --> 14:56.199
-MAKES YOU BLOAT.

14:57.418 --> 14:58.636
-DO I LOOK BLOATED TO YOU?

15:01.335 --> 15:04.555
-I'M IN TOO SERENE A STATE
TO ENGAGE IN A BLOAT DEBATE.

15:07.080 --> 15:09.212
-YOU REALIZE
THIS ISN'T WORKING, DON'T YOU?

15:09.343 --> 15:11.911
I MEAN, WE'VE BEEN
INVOLUNTARY ROOMMATES
FOR A WEEK NOW.

15:12.041 --> 15:14.609
AND I'M STARTING
TO BREAK OUT IN HIVES!

15:16.785 --> 15:18.526
-WELL, MAYBE IT'S BECAUSE
YOU DON'T EAT RIGHT.

15:21.659 --> 15:23.487
HERE, TRY SOME OF THIS.

15:23.618 --> 15:25.837
-NO, THANK YOU.
I CAN'T HARDLY STAND
TO WATCH YOU DRINK IT.

15:28.971 --> 15:31.495
-STEPHANIE, YOUR SYSTEM
IS POLLUTED.

15:34.150 --> 15:35.804
YOU SHOULD AT LEAST
CHANT WITH ME.

15:38.067 --> 15:39.590
-I DON'T WANT
TO CHANT WITH YOU.

15:40.722 --> 15:43.507
AND I CERTAINLY DON'T WANT
TO HAVE TO KEEP PICKING UP
AFTER YOU.

15:48.208 --> 15:49.470
-THEN WHY DO YOU
KEEP DOING IT?

15:50.123 --> 15:53.778
-BECAUSE I HATE WET CLOTHES
DRAPED OVER CHAIRS

15:53.909 --> 15:55.563
AND DOORS TO DRY!

15:57.043 --> 15:59.784
NEW INVENTION, C.J.--
LAUNDROMATS.

15:59.915 --> 16:02.657
WASHERS, DRYERS.
USE THEM.

16:03.527 --> 16:04.702
-DO YOU KNOW
WHAT DRYERS DO?

16:05.399 --> 16:08.184
DRYERS SEND OUT ALL KINDS
OF BAD ELEMENTS INTO THE AIR.

16:08.837 --> 16:10.882
NOT THE MENTION THE WASTE
OF ELECTRICITY.

16:13.189 --> 16:15.670
YOU KNOW, I HAVE A GREAT BOOK
ON SAVING THE ENVIRONMENT.

16:16.279 --> 16:17.498
I THINK YOU SHOULD READ IT.

16:18.368 --> 16:20.544
-HOW ABOUT ONE ON SAVING
MY SANITY?

16:21.545 --> 16:23.895
-SALT CAUSES HYPERTENSION,
YOU KNOW?

16:26.159 --> 16:27.638
-THEN MOVE
TO THE VICTIM'S HEAD,

16:28.204 --> 16:29.031
CHECK AIRWAY,

16:29.162 --> 16:30.728
TAKE A DEEP BREATH,

16:31.642 --> 16:33.035
SEAL OFF THE NOSE,

16:33.166 --> 16:35.690
AND DELIVER
TWO FULL LONG INFLATIONS,

16:35.820 --> 16:38.258
ONE TO ONE-AND-A-HALF SECONDS
IN DURATION.

16:38.388 --> 16:39.737
THEN MOVE BACK TO THE CHEST,

16:39.868 --> 16:41.739
LOCATE PROPER HAND POSITION,

16:41.870 --> 16:45.178
AND BEGIN
15 CARDIAC COMPRESSIONS.

16:46.135 --> 16:48.137
-HOW DO YOU LEARN THIS
WORD-FOR-WORD?

16:48.268 --> 16:49.921
-I JUST HAVE
ONE OF THOSE MEMORIES.

16:51.619 --> 16:53.751
-YOU KNOW, I NEVER REALIZED
YOU HAD TO LEARN SO MUCH

16:53.882 --> 16:55.014
TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

16:55.623 --> 16:57.973
-YEAH. DO YOU WANT
SOMETHING TO DRINK?

16:58.104 --> 17:00.541
-YEAH, GIVE ME
ONE OF THOSE SMART DRINKS

17:00.671 --> 17:02.499
AND MAKE IT A DOUBLE.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.893
-JUST TRY TO VISUALIZE
THE WHOLE PAGE IN
YOUR MIND'S EYE.

17:09.332 --> 17:10.942
-"THEN MOVE
TO THE VICTIM'S HEAD."

17:12.291 --> 17:14.816
-THE BEACH IS BEAUTIFUL
IN THE MORNING, ISN'T IT?

17:15.469 --> 17:17.252
I'M AARON BRODY,
MATTHEW'S FATHER.

17:17.384 --> 17:18.646
AND YOU ARE?

17:18.776 --> 17:19.907
-SUMMER QUINN.
PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

17:20.039 --> 17:22.432
-SUMMER.
WHAT AN ENCHANTING NAME.

17:24.347 --> 17:28.134
HUH. AND WHY DOES
A BEAUTIFUL YOUNG LADY
LIKE YOU

17:30.788 --> 17:32.355
WANT TO BECOME
A LIFEGUARD?

17:33.226 --> 17:35.010
-WELL, ACTUALLY,
MR. BRODY, I--

17:35.141 --> 17:37.621
PLEASE, CALL ME AARON.

17:39.319 --> 17:42.148
-WELL, LIFEGUARDING
IS SOMETHING I THINK
I WOULD BE GOOD AT.

17:42.278 --> 17:44.193
AND I REALLY NEED THE MONEY.

17:44.976 --> 17:46.674
-DO YOU LIVE ALONE?

17:47.892 --> 17:49.416
SUPPORT YOURSELF?

17:50.025 --> 17:51.592
-NO, I LIVE WITH MY MOM.

17:51.722 --> 17:53.594
WE JUST MOVED OUT HERE
FROM PITTSBURGH.

17:53.724 --> 17:56.858
WE'VE ALWAYS
KIND OF BEEN, YOU KNOW,
A TWO-INCOME FAMILY.

17:57.511 --> 18:00.209
-SO YOUR PARENTS
ARE DIVORCED?

18:01.384 --> 18:03.517
WELL, THAT'S AWFUL.
WHAT HAPPENED?

18:03.647 --> 18:06.781
-DAD, KNOCK IT OFF.
DON'T ANSWER HIM.

18:06.911 --> 18:09.479
-MATT, I THINK YOUR DAD
WAS JUST TRYING TO BE POLITE.

18:09.610 --> 18:11.568
-NO, HE'S JUST TRYING
TO PROBE YOU FOR MATERIAL.

18:12.178 --> 18:15.311
EVERYONE HE MEETS
IS JUST RESEARCH FOR
ONE OF HIS NOVELS OR SCRIPTS.

18:16.225 --> 18:17.574
LAY OFF MY FRIENDS, OKAY?

18:19.489 --> 18:22.057
-MY SON IS UNCOMFORTABLE
WITH HONEST DIALOGUE.

18:25.365 --> 18:27.280
-UH, MATT, I THINK
WE BETTER GET TO THE POOL.

18:27.976 --> 18:29.108
-GO AHEAD.
I'LL SEE YOU THERE.

18:30.674 --> 18:31.936
-DON'T GET TOO ATTACHED
TO MY SON.

18:32.067 --> 18:33.547
HE HAS A PROBLEM
WITH COMMITMENT.

18:34.548 --> 18:36.289
IT WAS A PLEASURE
MEETING YOU, SUMMER.

18:37.812 --> 18:39.466
-CLASS STARTS AT 10:00,
OKAY, MATT?

