21:12.488 --> 21:14.360
♪ SEE IT ALL

21:16.057 --> 21:18.581
♪ BREAK THE SURFACE

21:21.454 --> 21:24.239
-THAT DEMONSTRATION
WAS TO SHOW YOU
WHAT IT'S LIKE

21:25.153 --> 21:27.416
WHEN A KILLER RIPTIDE
TURNS THE BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN

21:27.547 --> 21:28.765
INTO A SANDSTORM.

21:29.418 --> 21:31.768
SOMETIMES YOU CAN'T EVEN SEE
THE SUBMERGED VICTIM.

21:32.508 --> 21:34.945
QUESTION--
WHAT WOULD YOU DO

21:35.468 --> 21:37.208
IN A RESCUE
UNDER A PIER

21:37.339 --> 21:39.602
IF A WAVE
WAS ABOUT TO SLAM YOU

21:40.342 --> 21:42.736
AND YOUR VICTIM
UP AGAINST THE PILING?

21:43.606 --> 21:44.433
CLINT?

21:47.262 --> 21:49.308
-PUT MY BODY BETWEEN
THE VICTIM AND THE PILING.

21:50.483 --> 21:51.353
-THE OPPOSITE.

21:52.789 --> 21:54.704
PUT THE VICTIM
BETWEEN YOU AND THE PILING,

21:54.835 --> 21:56.750
BECAUSE IF YOU GET HURT,
YOU BOTH MIGHT DROWN.

21:57.446 --> 21:58.317
LIEUTENANT?

21:59.970 --> 22:02.016
-THIS IS YOUR LIFE'S BLOOD,

22:02.146 --> 22:03.887
ON THE BEACH
AND IN THE OCEAN.

22:04.018 --> 22:05.498
TAKE IT WITH YOU
EVERYWHERE.

22:05.628 --> 22:07.326
WHEN YOU APPROACH A VICTIM,
YOU MUST...

22:08.152 --> 22:09.980
OFFER THEM THE CAN FIRST.

22:10.111 --> 22:11.765
IF THE VICTIM
APPROACHES YOU,

22:11.895 --> 22:13.244
YOU MUST BLOCK AND PARRY.

22:14.071 --> 22:14.985
TAKE THE CAN.

22:15.595 --> 22:17.336
-[GRUNTING]

22:18.293 --> 22:19.381
-YOU'RE LATE, MR. BRODY.

22:19.512 --> 22:20.643
-I'M SORRY.

22:21.862 --> 22:23.646
-IS THAT WHAT YOU'D SAY
IF YOU WERE LATE TO A RESCUE

22:23.777 --> 22:26.127
AND SOMEBODY DROWNED?
-[SPEAKING FRENCH]

22:29.391 --> 22:31.262
-I UNDERSTAND FRENCH,
MR. BRODY.

22:33.395 --> 22:34.353
GET IN THE POOL.

22:39.706 --> 22:42.448
THERE'S NOT ONE OF YOU
I CAN'T TOTALLY DOMINATE
IN THE WATER.

22:43.536 --> 22:45.886
NOT ONE OF YOU
WHO COULD THREATEN MY LIFE
WITH MERE STRENGTH.

22:46.800 --> 22:48.105
BECAUSE I KNOW
HOW TO PROTECT MYSELF

22:48.671 --> 22:49.759
AND THE LIFE
OF MY VICTIM.

22:56.810 --> 22:57.724
RESCUE ME.

23:28.232 --> 23:29.973
-[MATT COUGHING]

23:30.104 --> 23:32.715
-LEARN THESE LESSONS
HERE AND NOW

23:32.846 --> 23:35.936
BEFORE YOUR LIFE
AND YOUR VICTIM'S LIFE
IS ON THE LINE.

23:38.547 --> 23:40.810
THANK YOU FOR ILLUSTRATING
MY POINT SO WELL.

23:49.515 --> 23:50.690
-YOU WERE A LITTLE ROUGH
ON HIM.

23:52.474 --> 23:54.824
-OUR JOB IS TO WEED OUT
THE ONES WHO DON'T HAVE
WHAT IT TAKES.

23:54.955 --> 23:56.913
-IT'S ALSO TO HELP THE ONES
WHO HAVE WHAT IT TAKES,

23:57.044 --> 23:58.175
BUT DON'T KNOW IT YET.

24:09.404 --> 24:12.233
YOU KNOW, YOU HAVE
EVERYTHING INSIDE OF YOU
TO BE A GREAT LIFEGUARD.

24:12.363 --> 24:14.409
-HOW IN THE HELL DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I HAVE INSIDE ME?

24:14.540 --> 24:16.150
-BECAUSE WHEN YOU RUN,
YOU LET IT OUT.

24:16.280 --> 24:17.630
WHEN YOU SWIM,
YOU LET IT OUT.

24:18.326 --> 24:19.675
MATT, YOU'VE GOT
THE POTENTIAL

24:19.806 --> 24:21.416
OF BEATING EVERY
OTHER ROOKIE IN THAT SCHOOL.

24:22.373 --> 24:24.245
DON'T LET LIEUTENANT HOLDEN
BEAT YOU.

24:24.375 --> 24:25.855
-LIEUTENANT HOLDEN?

24:26.552 --> 24:28.597
APPARENTLY,
SHE KNOWS EVERYTHING, RIGHT?

24:28.728 --> 24:30.469
-YOU COULD LEARN
A LOT FROM HER.

24:30.599 --> 24:31.948
-YEAH, I JUST DID.

24:32.645 --> 24:34.342
I DID OUT THERE.

24:34.473 --> 24:36.431
I LEARNED THAT I DON'T WANT
TO BE A LIFEGUARD ANYMORE.

24:48.574 --> 24:51.402
-STEREO:
THE SUBJUGATION
OF PLEASURE, PART ONE.

24:52.491 --> 24:53.970
TO FULLY UNDERSTAND
THE REVOLUTIONARY...

24:54.101 --> 24:55.145
-C.J.:
OH, LEONARD.

24:57.017 --> 24:58.540
OH, THAT FEELS
SO GOOD.

24:58.671 --> 25:00.586
-STEREO:
THE EROGENOUS ZONES
OF THE 90S

25:00.716 --> 25:01.543
ARE MORE CLOSELY LINKED
TO EMOTION...

25:01.674 --> 25:02.544
-C.J.:
YES.

25:03.458 --> 25:05.373
OH MY GOD,
THAT FEELS SO GOOD.

25:05.504 --> 25:06.983
-STEREO:
THOUGHT OF
AS EROTIC...

25:12.598 --> 25:15.122
THAT THE SOURCE
OF PLEASURE CAN BE FOUND...

25:15.992 --> 25:18.604
WHEN WE EMBRACE EACH OTHER
WE NO LONGER NEED

25:18.734 --> 25:21.737
TO BE TIED
TO DESPERATE GROPING.

25:25.001 --> 25:27.613
MASSAGE THE ARMS
OR STROKE THE FOOT

25:27.743 --> 25:30.746
AND DERIVE FAR MORE PLEASURE
THAN IS OBTAINABLE...

25:30.877 --> 25:33.749
-UM, I'LL JUST GO
TO MY ROOM.

25:35.011 --> 25:37.797
-STEREO:
SENSUAL AREAS
THAT REMAIN SO FIXATED UPON

25:37.927 --> 25:39.320
IN THE AMERICAN PSYCHE.

25:43.280 --> 25:45.805
-LEONARD, I ENJOYED
OUR EVENING VERY, VERY MUCH.

25:45.935 --> 25:46.936
-GREAT.

25:51.332 --> 25:52.420
YOU INSPIRE ME.

25:53.029 --> 25:54.770
-I'LL FALL ASLEEP
LISTENING TO YOUR TAPE.

25:56.163 --> 25:57.294
SWEET DREAMS, LEONARD.

26:02.865 --> 26:05.172
STEPHANIE, RED MEANS STOP.

26:05.302 --> 26:06.608
-WHAT WOULD YOU
BE DOING RIGHT NOW

26:06.739 --> 26:07.957
IF I DIDN'T COME HOME
WHEN I DID, HUH?

26:08.088 --> 26:09.611
I MEAN, RIGHT THIS SECOND,
WHAT--

26:10.481 --> 26:13.397
-STEPHANIE,
HE IS INCREDIBLE.

26:13.528 --> 26:15.922
I MET HIM AT A BOOK SIGNING
AND I THOUGHT HE WAS
A TOTAL NERD.

26:16.052 --> 26:17.445
-HE IS.
-DOESN'T MATTER.

26:17.576 --> 26:20.622
HE IS THE SEXIEST MAN
I HAVE EVER MET.

26:20.753 --> 26:22.624
AT DINNER,
HE WAS EXPLAINING TO ME

26:22.755 --> 26:24.887
THE EROGENOUS MYTH
AND ITS RELATIONSHIP

26:25.018 --> 26:28.412
TO NEGLECTED AREAS
OF THE FEMALE ANATOMY.

26:31.546 --> 26:34.244
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN, AREAS?
I MEAN, LIKE, WHICH ONES?

26:34.897 --> 26:36.769
-WELL, IF YOU HADN'T
COME HOME WHEN YOU DID,

26:36.899 --> 26:38.684
HE PROBABLY
WOULD HAVE WORKED HIS WAY

26:38.814 --> 26:41.121
ALL THE WAY DOWN
TO MY HAND.

26:42.252 --> 26:44.037
-[LAUGHS]
WHERE'D HE START?

26:44.167 --> 26:45.821
-MY UPPER ARM.

26:48.084 --> 26:49.520
-YOUR UPPER ARM?

26:51.871 --> 26:55.352
WELL, LUCKY FOR YOU
I CAME HOME WHEN I DID.

26:56.136 --> 26:57.920
I MEAN, WE WOULDN'T
HAVE WANTED HIM TO GET
ALL THE WAY

26:58.051 --> 26:59.922
DOWN TO YOUR FINGERS
ON THE FIRST DATE,
NOW WOULD WE?

27:02.446 --> 27:03.665
SO DID YOU GUYS
BRING HOME ANYTHING?

27:03.796 --> 27:05.145
I'M STARVING.

27:13.153 --> 27:14.067
-OH.

27:20.247 --> 27:22.075
-[ALL CHATTERING]

27:22.205 --> 27:23.337
-HELLO.

27:29.604 --> 27:31.693
WHO AUTHORIZED THE PURCHASE
OF A NEW BLACKBOARD?

27:36.306 --> 27:37.220
DESKS?

27:38.395 --> 27:39.701
CHAIRS?
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

27:41.398 --> 27:42.617
-IT'S NOT NEW.

27:42.748 --> 27:44.750
I TAKE THE OLD
AND MAKE IT LOOK NEW.

27:44.880 --> 27:48.362
OH, I SPENT DAY AND NIGHT
WORKING AND POLISHING
AND CLEANING

27:48.492 --> 27:50.669
AND POLISHING AND CLEANING
AND CLEANING AND CLEANING

27:50.799 --> 27:52.671
JUST TO MAKE IT
LOOK BEAUTIFUL FOR YOU.

27:53.889 --> 27:55.064
-GUIDO, THANK YOU.

27:55.195 --> 27:56.849
-OH, THE PLEASURE,
SHE'S ALL MINE.

27:57.501 --> 27:59.112
-WELL, KEEP UP
THE GOOD WORK.

28:01.070 --> 28:02.724
-[ALL GIGGLING]

28:05.031 --> 28:07.468
-WELL, CONGRATULATIONS
TO THOSE OF YOU

28:07.598 --> 28:09.775
WHO MADE IT TO THIS LAST DAY
OF ROOKIE SCHOOL.

28:10.645 --> 28:12.691
YOUR LAST TEST
WILL BE THE GAUNTLET.

28:12.821 --> 28:15.084
IT WILL BE HARDER
THAN THE FIRST TIME
YOU RAN IT.

28:15.215 --> 28:17.521
THE DUMMIES WILL BE HEAVIER
AND FARTHER OUT IN THE WATER.

28:17.652 --> 28:20.524
THE RUN WILL BE LONGER
AND THE PIER JUMP HIGHER.

28:21.264 --> 28:22.396
BUT I KNOW YOU CAN DO IT.

28:23.049 --> 28:24.485
YOU'VE WORKED HARD
THESE LAST TWO WEEKS,

28:24.615 --> 28:25.878
REALLY HARD.

28:26.400 --> 28:28.968
SO GO OUT THERE
AND GO GET 'EM.

28:40.893 --> 28:42.372
-MAY I HELP YOU?

28:42.503 --> 28:44.853
-YEAH, MY NAME IS LIEUTENANT
MITCH BUCHANNON.

28:44.984 --> 28:47.334
I'M LOOKING FOR MATT BRODY.

28:47.464 --> 28:49.031
-WELL, THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

28:49.945 --> 28:51.773
MATTHEW DIDN'T COME HOME
LAST NIGHT.

28:51.904 --> 28:53.296
-PLEASE, COME IN.

28:55.516 --> 28:56.343
HAVE A SEAT.

28:56.473 --> 28:57.474
-THANK YOU.

29:01.304 --> 29:03.567
AS YOU PROBABLY KNOW,
MATT'S ATTENDING
ROOKIE SCHOOL.

29:03.698 --> 29:05.569
AND WELL, HE HAD
A LITTLE PROBLEM

29:05.700 --> 29:08.659
WITH ONE OF OUR OTHER
LIEUTENANTS YESTERDAY
AND HE RAN OFF.

29:10.139 --> 29:12.228
-MATTHEW HAS A DIFFICULT TIME
WITH AUTHORITY.

29:12.359 --> 29:14.578
HE'S... SENSITIVE BOY.

29:16.189 --> 29:18.321
-I THINK MATTHEW NEEDS
TO ACCEPT RESPONSIBILITY

29:18.452 --> 29:20.149
FOR HIMSELF,
FOR HIS OWN BEHAVIOR.

29:20.889 --> 29:23.326
-AND YOU BELIEVE
THAT BECOMING A LIFEGUARD

29:23.457 --> 29:24.850
WILL HELP HIM
DEVELOP THAT?

29:24.980 --> 29:26.677
-ABSOLUTELY.

29:27.287 --> 29:29.637
WHEN YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE
FOR THE SAFETY OF THOUSANDS
OF PEOPLE ON THE BEACH,

29:29.768 --> 29:30.899
YOU HAVE TO BE RESPONSIBLE.

29:31.770 --> 29:33.902
-AND IF YOU'RE INCAPABLE
OF RESPONSIBILITY,

29:34.033 --> 29:36.165
YOU'D BE PUTTING
THOSE PEOPLE'S LIVES
IN DANGER, RIGHT?

29:37.950 --> 29:38.951
-MR. BRODY,

29:40.430 --> 29:41.649
I BELIEVE IN MATT.

29:43.129 --> 29:45.871
GIVEN HALF A CHANCE,
I THINK HE COULD START
BELIEVING IN HIMSELF.

29:48.961 --> 29:50.440
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE I MIGHT FIND HIM?

29:50.571 --> 29:52.051
I'D SURE LIKE
TO TALK TO HIM.
-YES.

29:52.616 --> 29:54.227
OFF GETTING IN TROUBLE
SOMEWHERE.

29:55.706 --> 29:57.360
-HE MAY HAVE GONE SURFING.

29:57.491 --> 29:58.927
HIS BOARD WAS MISSING
THIS MORNING.

29:59.754 --> 30:00.755
-THANK YOU.

30:12.898 --> 30:14.029
MATT, WAIT UP.

30:16.553 --> 30:17.903
-HOW'D YOU FIND ME?

30:18.033 --> 30:19.600
-I JUST CAME
FROM YOUR HOUSE.

30:20.340 --> 30:21.863
HAD A LITTLE TALK
WITH YOUR PARENTS.

30:22.864 --> 30:25.562
-MY FATHER GIVES NEW MEANING
TO THE PHRASE "FAMILY MAN,"
DOESN'T HE?

30:25.693 --> 30:27.260
-[CHUCKLES]

30:27.390 --> 30:30.176
HE THINKS YOU'RE A QUITTER.
-WHAT DO YOU THINK?

30:31.177 --> 30:32.352
-I THINK YOU'RE AFRAID
TO WIN.

30:32.482 --> 30:34.223
-I'M NOT AFRAID OF ANYTHING.

30:34.354 --> 30:35.181
-THEN SHOW ME!

30:35.311 --> 30:36.965
SHOW YOUR DAD.

30:38.749 --> 30:39.794
SHOW YOURSELF.

30:40.490 --> 30:42.536
-WHY IS MY BEING A LIFEGUARD
SO IMPORTANT TO YOU?

30:44.016 --> 30:46.670
-BECAUSE YOU REMIND ME
OF A YOUNG HOTHEAD
I ONCE KNEW

30:47.497 --> 30:48.803
WHO HAD A PROBLEM
WITH HIS DAD.

30:48.934 --> 30:50.370
-EDDIE KRAMER?

30:52.111 --> 30:52.938
-NO.

30:54.635 --> 30:56.550
THIS ONE
WAS ABOUT A FOOT TALLER.

31:00.075 --> 31:01.772
THE GAUNTLET STARTS
IN AN HOUR,

31:02.991 --> 31:04.471
WITH OR WITHOUT YOU.

31:28.408 --> 31:31.454
-OKAY, TODAY YOU RUN
THE GAUNTLET AGAINST
THE CLOCK.

31:31.585 --> 31:33.108
IT'LL BE
A STAGGERED START.

31:33.717 --> 31:34.805
TWO MINUTES
BETWEEN EACH GROUP.

31:40.115 --> 31:41.334
DAMN IT.

31:44.859 --> 31:45.816
GO AHEAD.

31:46.600 --> 31:49.211
-OKAY, GROUP ONE,
GO TO THE STARTING LINE.

31:55.783 --> 31:58.046
-[ALL CHEERING]

32:11.233 --> 32:13.105
-I'M SORRY I'M LATE AGAIN,
LIEUTENANT HOLDEN.

32:13.235 --> 32:15.455
IT WILL NEVER
HAPPEN AGAIN.

32:20.416 --> 32:21.374
-JOIN GROUP TWO.

32:22.375 --> 32:23.463
-THANK YOU.

36:00.375 --> 36:01.463
-JUMP!

36:04.640 --> 36:05.641
-SUMMER!

36:06.338 --> 36:07.991
SUMMER, JUMP!
EVERYONE'S PASSING YOU.

36:08.122 --> 36:09.471
JUMP!

36:22.310 --> 36:24.138
SUMMER, TAKE MY HAND.
WE'LL JUMP TOGETHER.

36:24.269 --> 36:26.096
-NO, I CAN'T DO THIS.
-YES, YOU CAN, COME ON.

36:28.490 --> 36:29.491
COME ON.

36:31.711 --> 36:33.191
-WHAT'S THE MATTER, BRODY?
YOU CAN'T MAKE IT?

36:34.235 --> 36:35.715
JUST NEED AN EXCUSE TO LOSE,
HUH?

36:44.898 --> 36:46.943
-COME ON, DON'T LET HIM WIN.
YOU COULD BEAT HIM.

36:47.074 --> 36:48.510
-I'M NOT JUMPING
WITHOUT YOU.

36:48.641 --> 36:50.338
-LOOK, IF I CAN'T
DO THIS BY MYSELF,

36:50.469 --> 36:52.035
I DON'T DESERVE
TO MAKE IT.

36:52.166 --> 36:54.560
-LOOK, WE'LL DO IT TOGETHER.
WE'LL JUMP TOGETHER.

36:54.690 --> 36:57.040
OKAY?
ON THREE.

36:57.650 --> 37:01.001
ONE, TWO, THREE.

37:18.888 --> 37:20.238
-NOW GO GET CLINT!

37:20.368 --> 37:21.326
GO!

38:27.783 --> 38:30.656
-[ALL CHEERING]

39:01.034 --> 39:02.688
-OKAY, LISTEN UP.

39:03.341 --> 39:04.298
LET'S GO.

39:04.820 --> 39:06.561
WE ALL KNOW
YOU'RE ANXIOUS TO HEAR

39:06.692 --> 39:08.128
WHERE YOU'LL BE WORKING
THIS SUMMER.

39:09.042 --> 39:10.609
AS YOU KNOW,
THERE ARE 18 OF YOU

39:10.739 --> 39:13.351
AND THERE ARE
ONLY 13 POSITIONS OPEN.

39:14.003 --> 39:17.137
THE SELECTIONS WERE BASED
ON COMPETITIVE RESULTS,

39:17.267 --> 39:19.922
TEST SCORES,
AND ATTITUDE.

39:20.488 --> 39:21.881
LIEUTENANT HOLDEN?

39:22.490 --> 39:24.318
-THANK YOU.
THE ASSIGNMENTS
ARE AS FOLLOWS.

39:24.840 --> 39:26.320
ZUMA,
RILEY AND JOHNSON.

39:26.451 --> 39:28.670
-[ALL CHEERING]

39:31.325 --> 39:33.545
-TOPANGA,
BEGHES AND DOWLING.

39:33.675 --> 39:35.242
-[ALL CHEERING]

39:36.896 --> 39:38.898
-MANHATTAN,
KRIEGER AND PETERSON.

39:42.292 --> 39:44.773
HUNTINGTON,
HAGAR AND DWYER.

39:46.688 --> 39:48.995
AND BAYWATCH,
LEWISTON AND QUINN.

39:54.435 --> 39:56.002
LIEUTENANT BUCHANNON
WILL ANNOUNCE

39:56.132 --> 39:57.220
THE ROOKIE
OF THE YEAR.

39:57.830 --> 39:59.701
-OF THE SIX OF YOU REMAINING,

39:59.832 --> 40:03.139
I'M SORRY,
BUT FIVE WILL HAVE TO WAIT
UNTIL NEXT SUMMER.

40:04.010 --> 40:05.925
BUT I WOULD LIKE
TO THANK EVERYBODY

40:06.534 --> 40:09.363
FOR MAKING THIS POSSIBLY
THE BEST ROOKIE SCHOOL

40:09.494 --> 40:11.452
IN L.A. COUNTY
LIFEGUARD HISTORY.

40:18.503 --> 40:20.243
AS YOU ALL KNOW,
TRADITION STATES

40:21.070 --> 40:22.289
THE ROOKIE OF THE YEAR

40:23.116 --> 40:24.639
GETS HIS OR HER CHOICE

40:24.770 --> 40:26.815
OF WHERE THEY WORK.

40:28.077 --> 40:28.991
THIS YEAR,

40:29.601 --> 40:31.994
THAT CHOICE
GOES TO...

40:34.954 --> 40:35.911
MATTHEW BRODY.

40:38.784 --> 40:39.741
-THANK YOU.
-CONGRATULATIONS, MAN.

40:39.872 --> 40:40.699
-THANK YOU.

40:43.353 --> 40:44.485
-CONGRATULATIONS.

40:44.616 --> 40:46.139
-THANKS.
-YOUR UNSELFISH SUPPORT

40:46.269 --> 40:48.315
OF SUMMER ON THE PIER
SHOWED US A LOT.

40:49.098 --> 40:50.622
IT'S WHAT LIFEGUARDING
IS ALL ABOUT--

40:50.752 --> 40:52.972
BEING THERE FOR EACH OTHER,
BACKING EACH OTHER UP.

40:53.102 --> 40:54.452
-YEAH, I LEARNED THAT.

40:55.322 --> 40:57.629
-SO WHICH BEACH
